# Agent Collaboration Rules

Read `docs/agent_collaboration_standard.md` before multi-agent work on any Spec.

## SDD pipeline (mandatory)

This project follows **SDD** (Spec-Driven Development). Each Spec phase:

```text
Plan → Implementation → Test → Acceptance → Handoff → Final Review
```

Agent pipeline:

```text
TL Plan → Dev (whitelist) → DB Review → E2E QA → Handoff → TL Final Review
```

- No Plan / Tasks → no implementation.
- No DB pass → no QA.
- No QA pass → no merge-ready handoff.
- One writer per file per iteration. No skipping DB or QA.

## Role principles

| Role | Core duty | Hard ban |
|------|-----------|----------|
| **Tech Lead (`TL`)** | Scope, Plan, design review, **final review**. **No code.** | Write `backend/**`. Must **refuse** out-of-scope tasks. |
| **Dev (`DEV`)** | Code **only** within TL-approved file whitelist. **Read tasks.md first.** | SQL schema changes. Touch original files or **real raw_vault** artifacts. |
| **DB & Data (`DB`)** | Review SQL/ORM/data consistency only. Report idempotency, pollution, schema drift. | Edit business code (`backend/app/services/**`). |
| **E2E QA (`QA`)** | Test design, run commands, acceptance table. Check readonly, re-run, error recovery. | Edit business services to pass tests. |
| **Handoff (`HO`)** | Write `docs/handoff-*.md` only. Record commits, tests, done/undone, next-phase entry. | Code, specs, sql, or QA sign-off. |

Only **Dev Agent** may edit production Python, and **only** when explicitly in step ② Implementation with a TL file whitelist.

**Default rule**: Tech Lead / DB & Data / E2E QA / Handoff **must not** edit business code.

## Session start

Declare: role, Spec, branch, pipeline step, **TL file whitelist** (for DEV), blacklist.

Templates: `docs/role_prompts/`.

## Global prohibitions (all phases)

- Do not analyze **source-code repositories** (Java/Python/JS etc.) as KB assets.
- Do not move, delete, rename, or overwrite **original user files**.
- Do not **auto-delete duplicate files**.
- Do not delete **raw_vault** files (002 copies are append-only; idempotent skip if bin exists).
- Do not integrate **MinerU** or **MarkItDown** early (006 / 005+).
- Do not build **Parser Router** (004+), **`parsed/`**, **`curated/`**, **Streamlit** (012+), **vector DB** (011+), or **project-card distillation** early.
- Do not change **SQL schema** without Spec authorization and migration.
- Do not upload private documents to external cloud services by default.
- TL must refuse and narrow scope when tasks exceed the active Spec.

## 003 duplicate-governance constraints (when active)

- Exact **sha256** duplicates only — no semantic similarity dedup.
- Output `duplicate_report` and `cleanup_suggestion_report` only.
- **`auto_execute = false`** — suggestions only; no delete/move/rename/quarantine execution.
- No LLM master selection; use 001 `master_file_instance_uid`.
- Do not modify `inventory_scanner.py` or `file_content_vault.py`.

## Sealed services (003 default)

- `backend/app/services/inventory_scanner.py`
- `backend/app/services/file_content_vault.py`
